  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2021.06.1-alpha\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.10 (GNU/Linux 5.8.0-50-generic x86_64) (fully synched node)\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nerigon \\\r\n  --datadir \"/home/foo/erigon\" \\\r\n  --metrics \\\r\n  --txpool.globalslots 16384 \\\r\n  --txpool.globalqueue 4096\r\n\r\nrpcdaemon \\\r\n  --datadir \"home/foo/erigon\" \\\r\n  --private.api.addr=0.0.0.0:9090 \\\r\n  --http.api=eth,debug,net,web3,trace,erigon \\\r\n  --http.addr=0.0.0.0 \\\r\n  --metrics \\\r\n  --metrics.port=6070 \\\r\n  --ws\r\n ```\r\n\r\nCommit hash : -\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI expect the following RPC methods to work:\r\n- web3_clientVersion\r\n- net_version\r\n- eth_protocolVersion\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThey return with an error \"connection closed\".\r\n\r\nExamples of methods that do work as expeced: \r\n- net_listening\r\n- net_peerCount\r\n- eth_blockNumber\r\n- eth_syncing\r\n- erigon_forks\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nUse the Postman configuration as provided in the RPCDaemon documentation or use CURL directly\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nHTTP_IP=\"\"\r\n\r\ncurl --location --request POST $HTTP_IP --header 'Content-Type: application/json' --data-raw '{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\r\n  \"method\":\"web3_clientVersion\",\r\n  \"params\":[],\r\n  \"id\":1\r\n}'\r\n```",
